---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="ReadForge">
  <section>
    <div class="hero">
      <h2>Forge your own stories.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        ReadForge is a <strong>local-first Android app</strong> for creating and reading AI-assisted books.
        It helps you generate prompts, share them to the LLM app you prefer, and paste the results back into a structured library.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/cmwen/read-forge-app/releases/latest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download latest release</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="install/">Developer install</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/cmwen/read-forge-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card span-6">
        <h3>Core workflow</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Create a book (title/description/purpose are optional)</li>
          <li>Generate a prompt for TOC or a chapter</li>
          <li>Share the prompt to any LLM app (LLM-agnostic)</li>
          <li>Paste the response back to import and store locally</li>
          <li>Read with a full-featured reader</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="card span-6">
        <h3>What you get</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Local-first storage:</strong> your library lives on-device (SQLite/Drift)</li>
          <li><strong>LLM-agnostic:</strong> share to your preferred AI app</li>
          <li><strong>Reading tools:</strong> themes, bookmarks, highlights, and notes</li>
          <li><strong>Customizable prompts:</strong> writing style, tone, vocabulary, language</li>
          <li><strong>Export/import:</strong> backup and portability via JSON</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card span-12">
        <h3>Languages</h3>
        <p>ReadForge includes UI translations for 12 languages (including English, Spanish, Chinese, French, German, Portuguese, Japanese, Korean, Arabic, Hindi, and Russian).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
